news.headline: Consumer Price Index: Inflation Holds Steady At 2.7% In July, Lower Than Expected
news.summary: Inflation held steady in July as the headline figure for the Consumer Price Index was at 2.7% year-over-year, unchanged from June and lower than the expected 2.8% growth.

news.headline: Economic Optimism Returns Among Small Businesses
news.summary: After peaking post-election at 105.1 in December, the headline index went on to fall to a low of 95.8 in April and has since erased about half of that decline. Click to read.

news.headline: AIER's Everyday Price Index Notches A Slight 0.10% Gain In July 2025
news.summary: In July 2025, the AIER Everyday Price Index rose to 296.1, a rise of 0.10 percent. This is the eighth consecutive monthly increase in the index.

news.headline: Tariffs Causing Inflation? Not So Fast!
news.summary: July CPI reveals rising inflation, driven by durable goods & services. Read why I remain cautious about a September Fed rate cut.

news.headline: July CPI: Fuel And Housing Steal The Show
news.summary: July CPI at 2.7% signals real wage gains amid stable inflation trends. Explore key market shifts, rate cut predictions, and impacts on consumer spending.
